Product description

Lepow Portable Monitor Z1 Series


IPS Panel

Adopting a premium IPS panel with FHD 1080P resolution, delivering high-definition and extraordinary images from a 178 full viewing angle.


Dual Stereo Speakers

Built-in dual speakers deliver booming sound with crystal-clear audio quality and bring an enticing home theater experience to the comforts of your home.


Plug and Play

With two full-featured Type C input, this portable monitor easily connects to a variety of electronic devices, including laptops, smartphones, PCs, PS3/4, XBOX ONE, Switch, and more. It is ideal for extending your screen or playing games on a business trip, travel, or home entertainment.


Compatible with Cell Phones

Lepow external monitor is compatible with Type C phones that support full-featured output. Only a Type C cable is required to achieve the screen mirroring on the phone and monitor. You can expand your phone screen to work or play.


Ultra-Thin and Portable

The portable monitor for laptops and phones comes with a magnetic smart cover, which features a 0.3-inch profile and 1.7-pound weight, providing the greatest convenience for your daily business, travel, and entertainment.

Ideal for Business and Entertainment

The Lepow portable monitor in 3-in-1 mode easily connects to various laptops, smartphones, Switch, etc. for your convenience and pleasure.

FAQ

  • Why it doesn't work when I connect the Lepow monitor with my devices by USB Type-C cable?

1. Not all Type-C ports can support signals. Please check the Type-C port of your devices is full-function.

2. Please check the Type-C cable you used is a USB 3.1 Gen2 cable (the original one) or not. Your own cable may be only a charging cable.

  • What should I do if my Lepow monitor keeps flashing/restarting?

Flashing or continuously restarting is usually caused by not enough power supply. Please plug in the wall charger to the Type-C port of the monitor for enough power supply (5V/2A or above).

  • Does my iPhone/iPad work with the Lepow monitor by the Apple charging cable?

No, it doesn't work. If you want to connect the monitor to your iPhone/iPad, you need a lightning to HDMI adapter.

  • I have charged my Lepow monitor for several hours. Why does it fail to turn on?

The Lepow monitor does not have a built-in battery. Before connecting the monitor, please make sure it has enough power (5V/2A or above) coming in firstly.

    A great second monitor for travel
    Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2019
    Color: Black(2*Type-C+HDMI)
    1.
    I'm an instructional designer and 3D jewelry artist, and I literally dreamed of having a second monitor for traveling. I had originally purchased my top-of-the-line MacBook Pro to make instructional ZBrush CAD videos, but the fan runs constantly and it's picked up... See more
    I'm an instructional designer and 3D jewelry artist, and I literally dreamed of having a second monitor for traveling. I had originally purchased my top-of-the-line MacBook Pro to make instructional ZBrush CAD videos, but the fan runs constantly and it's picked up on any external microphone. My idea to place my MacBook off the table and record from an external monitor seemed to be the right solution. I also found that the Retina display on the Mac causes Camtasia to record video at a much higher resolution that has to be downsampled, making the software interface blurry. I needed to record at a native 1920x1080 resolution.

    Unboxing was very "Apple-y." If you've ever bought an Apple product, the heavyweight box, the packaging reinforces that you've just bought something special. They include a nice instruction book that's got lots of pictures...sometimes when you buy something from a manufacturer in the Far East, the instructions are not well-written. Lepow's instruction manual feels familiar and is nicely done...it's very clear.

    Anyway, this portable monitor does the trick. I bought it on a whim for Black Friday because the price was in my budget, but even at full price it's a nice monitor. If I'd seen it before buying, I would have paid full price, but taking a chance on a new product and company I'm not familiar with, the price was worth taking a chance on. I also see that Amazon may have a coupon...look for that as well.

    I also LOVE that it's powered by the USB-C port on my MacBook Pro and doesn't require a power cord to run from the USB-C port, although I finally read the instructions, and they suggest plugging it in...if you don't, the monitor comes up not at full brightness, but at least on a MBP with USB-C, it does work. The folding cover makes it feel like I'm carrying a large iPad, and it seems to protect it well. The only thing that I'd like to see changed is the "roll" button for changing the settings. I cannot figure out how to jump from the main menu to the individual setting items...I've tried, but still trying to figure it out...there's got to be a trick that I'm missing. There is a left column of main settings, and it says to press the roll key to activate the menu, scroll the roll key up and down to choose a setting, then press the roll key to confirm. There needs to be a little more information about this in the little book, about how to change columns.

    I was WAY overcomplicating the stand, too. I was trying to fold it like an iPad...and I was overthinking it. It's attached magnetically to the back of the monitor, folded in an "L" configuration (kind of like a Lexus logo...), then the monitor sets in one of two grooves for two different viewing positions.

    Also, be aware that the two USB-C ports are not the same. One is a full-functioning USB-C port (on the left), and the one on the right is for power only. When I connect my MacBook Pro to the left USB-C port only, and the MBP is plugged in, it works just fine without external power. That is my experience with the MBP, so I don't know if that applies to a PC notebook. It comes with all of the cords that you'll need to connect, including a USB-C cable, HDMI cable, and a power source cable. If you were on your way to a hotel or conference and decided to have this delivered, you won't be searching around for a Best Buy at closing time to find cables.

    Overall, I'm extremely happy with this monitor...it's already making my life easier! I'd say if you're on the fence, give it a shot. You won't be disappointed. It's got a generous viewing area and the portability is perfect.

    4.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    Great Monitor!
    Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2019
    Color: Black(2*Type-C+HDMI)
    My wife bought this monitor for me because I like to sit on my deck, have a cigar and watch sports. Normally, I use my old iPad for this, but the screen is a little small for viewing sports and the picture isn't up to today's standards. This monitor is so much... See more
    My wife bought this monitor for me because I like to sit on my deck, have a cigar and watch sports. Normally, I use my old iPad for this, but the screen is a little small for viewing sports and the picture isn't up to today's standards. This monitor is so much better. The screen size is great and the picture is really good. It works great for what I'm going to use it for, but also works great as an extra monitor for my Macbook Air.

    There are a couple downsides though. First, the volume isnt loud enough. You can set it using the settings scroll wheel on the side, but even when set to 100, its still not very loud. At least there are speakers on both sides, so it is stereo. Second, the monitor doesn't have an internal battery. You can power it from a PC/Macbook, but my iPhone XS Max could not power it. It does come with a USB-C power cord and plugin adapter, but the cord is only 1M, so you need to be close to a power outlet, use an extension cord, or purchase a longer USB-C cord. A larger portable battery might do the job, but my older Mophie couldnt hack it.

    The primary reason for this review is to let you iPhone/iPad users know what you need to get this to work. It will not work using only the included cables. You will need to purchase the Apple Digital AV to Lightening adapter ($49 from Apple. Note: Buy the Apple manufactured adapter, so you don't run into compatibility issues). This has the female HDMI and Lightening ports on one end and a male Lightening port on the other. Don't buy the Apple USB-C to Lightening adapter. That was a $20 mistake for me; it won't work for this.

    Once you have that Apple adapter, plug in the HDMI to mini-HDMI cable (Included with the monitor) into the Apple adapter, then plug the Lightening connector into your iPhone or iPad. Connect your power USB-C cord to a power outlet and you're in business. Note: The power cord has to use the right-hand side USB-C port.

    Connecting to a PC or Macbook uses the included USB-C to USB-C or HDMI to mini-HDMI cables. Nothing else is required.

    Finally, I've seen differing comments on compatible streaming services. I use the following apps and they all worked: Hulu Live TV, Netflix, Amazon Prime Video, and YouTube (regular YT app. I don't have YouTube TV). It will also mirror your phone for apps like Twitter, Instagram, Facebook, etc. It's not full monitor size, but is larger than the iPhone display.

    Hopefully this will be helpful for some of you. I just got the cable scheme figured out yesterday, so I haven't had a lot of time to use it, but so far I'm very happy with it and would recommend it.

    This monitor generally works as advertised, and is easy to use with just one cable needed to connect it to a USB-C capable computer and also power it (I have a Mac).

While you can use the screen in both orientations, the monitor won't stand stably using just the stand -- you'd need some extra support to make sure it won't tip over.
